 class HistogramDistance
          Histogram distance using L2 metric,(defined as D(x,y) = sum ((xi -yi)^2) This is YA distance for Nearest Neighbor algorithms

 class KendallCorrelationDistance

 class KendallCorrelationTauBDistance
          This was implemented because the Kendall tau rank correlation showed promise This runs in N long N time unlike the simple implementation This version also takes ties of X Y and (X,Y) into account making to closest to the Tau-B The original impl calculated the Tau-A
 class KeseljWeightedDistance
          Histogram distance as weighted by Keselj (2003).
 class KullbackLeiblerDivergence

 class LevenshteinDistance
          LevenshteinDistance, the edit-distance between two sequences of Events.
 class LZWDivergence

 class ManhattanDistance

 class MeanDistance
          Mean Distance or normalized dot product.
 class NominalKSDistance
          Nominal Kolmogorov-Smirnov distance for Nearest Neighbor algorithm
 class PearsonCorrelationDistance
          PearsonCorrelationDistance : Parametric equivalent of KendallCorrelationDistance, based on Pearson's product-moment correlation General theory: Pearson's correlation measures how similar frequency rankings are between two rank orderings; +1 is perfect agreement, -1 is perfect disagreement.
